staring at it all night.

24
00:04:08,770 --> 00:04:10,032
Emily, hon, I got it.

25
00:04:12,948 --> 00:04:15,951
Just meet me in the lobby.
I'll be a minute. Okay?

26
00:04:19,215 --> 00:04:20,260
Sure.

27
00:04:31,358 --> 00:04:32,446
[EXHALES]

28
00:04:34,796 --> 00:04:36,406
Danny, what the hell.

29
00:04:53,031 --> 00:04:54,119
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

30
00:04:59,168 --> 00:05:00,300
Hello.

31
00:05:00,343 --> 00:05:02,214
-LOGAN: Is Tony there?
-Yes, he is.

32
00:05:02,258 --> 00:05:05,348
But we're on vacation
and we're actually trying
to get away from things.

33
00:05:05,392 --> 00:05:06,958
Can't this wait
until we get back?

34
00:05:07,002 --> 00:05:10,092
I'd rather not, ma'am.
It's an urgent matter.

35
00:05:12,442 --> 00:05:16,577
It's Logan. He says
he needs to talk to you
right away.

36
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:19,231
I think you should take it
before he has a stroke
or something.

37
00:05:20,842 --> 00:05:22,409
Hey, Tony... Sir.

38
00:05:22,452 --> 00:05:25,150
There's a reason
why my cell phone is off.
Now make it quick.

39
00:05:25,194 --> 00:05:27,588
We have dinner reservations
in 15 minutes.

40
00:05:27,631 --> 00:05:30,721
Sorry to bother you,
but I'm kind of freaked out.

41
00:05:30,765 --> 00:05:31,896
I'm not sure what to do.

42
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:33,942
What's this all about, Logan?

43
00:05:33,985 --> 00:05:39,469
LOGAN: Well, I met
with Danny last night
at Belleau Street store.

44
00:05:39,513 --> 00:05:43,778
He, uh... He told me
to come with him
to his house and...

45
00:05:43,821 --> 00:05:47,434
uh, wait in the garage
until he needed my help.

46
00:05:47,477 --> 00:05:53,570
So, you know, uh,
I did that, but then
I fell asleep.

47
00:05:53,614 --> 00:05:57,531
I don't know what Danny did,
but he woke me up this morning,

48
00:05:57,574 --> 00:06:00,229
told me I had to leave
right away, so I did.

49
00:06:00,272 --> 00:06:04,712
But he was acting real...
strange, spooky, you know?

50
00:06:04,755 --> 00:06:07,367
-I... I think
you ought to call him.
-[LINE DISCONNECTS]

51
00:06:07,410 --> 00:06:09,673
[LINE RINGING]

52
00:06:11,588 --> 00:06:12,981
BILL: Tony.
TONY: Bill.

53
00:06:13,024 --> 00:06:15,810
Really glad I reached you.
I need a big favor.

54
00:06:15,853 --> 00:06:18,639
Danny left me a really
strange message last night.

55
00:06:18,682 --> 00:06:20,162
I need you to get ahold of him.

56
00:06:20,205 --> 00:06:22,251
BILL: You got it, bud.

57
00:06:22,294 --> 00:06:25,515
Yeah, I'm in my truck right now.
I'm heading to the gym,
so I'll just swing by.

58
00:06:25,559 --> 00:06:27,169
I'll call you back
in a few minutes.

59
00:06:27,212 --> 00:06:28,736
I'm sure everything is okay.

60
00:06:29,563 --> 00:06:31,216
Yeah, I'll check it out.

61
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:33,654
Ciao, boss. Hey, stop worrying.

62
00:06:34,611 --> 00:06:35,699
Jeez.

63
00:06:42,576 --> 00:06:44,404
I have a bad feeling this time.

64
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,395
[PERSON BREATHING HEAVILY]

65
00:07:32,887 --> 00:07:36,238
-[DIALING]
-[LINE RINGING]

66
00:07:36,281 --> 00:07:38,458
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

67
00:07:42,287 --> 00:07:44,768
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]
-[DOORBELL RINGING]

68
00:07:44,812 --> 00:07:46,509
BILL: Danny? Rachel?
Is anybody home?

69
00:07:46,553 --> 00:07:48,511
