You've reached Rachel.

70
00:07:48,555 --> 00:07:49,686
DANNY: Danny.
EVAN: Evan.

71
00:07:49,730 --> 00:07:51,079
CHRISTOPHER: And Christopher.

72
00:07:51,122 --> 00:07:52,907
-ALL: Please leave a message.
-[BEEP]

73
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:55,518
Hello. Danny?

74
00:07:55,562 --> 00:07:57,302
[PERSON BREATHING HEAVILY]

75
00:07:57,346 --> 00:07:59,087
Rachel. Anybody home?

76
00:08:03,787 --> 00:08:05,833
Hey, it's Bill Schroeder.
Can you let me in?

77
00:08:10,794 --> 00:08:12,883
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

78
00:08:17,366 --> 00:08:18,846
Chris, where are
your mom and dad?

79
00:08:34,731 --> 00:08:36,951
-Go.
-Watch it, watch it.

80
00:08:36,994 --> 00:08:38,735
-Go.
-Take the shot.

81
00:08:41,651 --> 00:08:42,739
-[MAN EXCLAIMS]
-Nice shot.

82
00:08:42,783 --> 00:08:43,784
Airball.

83
00:08:44,654 --> 00:08:45,742
Uh, ball in.

84
00:08:47,962 --> 00:08:49,746
MAN: Attack! Attack!

85
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:51,531
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

86
00:08:54,621 --> 00:08:55,622
MAN 1: Junior.

87
00:08:58,581 --> 00:09:01,453
MAN 2: Go, you go!
We good! We good!

88
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,675
CAROLYN: You have a good day,
buddy, all right?

89
00:09:05,719 --> 00:09:07,895
Have a good soccer game.
Score a goal for me.

90
00:09:07,938 --> 00:09:09,070
-See ya.
-All right.

91
00:09:09,113 --> 00:09:11,028
-Bye, sweetheart.
-Bye, Mom.

92
00:09:11,942 --> 00:09:13,248
Bye, guys!

93
00:09:19,297 --> 00:09:20,995
[SIGHS]

94
00:09:24,825 --> 00:09:26,391
Embarrassing, dude.

95
00:09:26,435 --> 00:09:27,828
MAN: Over here, over here!

96
00:09:41,929 --> 00:09:43,757
-[PHONE RINGING]
-Ooh.

97
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:50,938
Hey, how was your morning?

98
00:09:50,981 --> 00:09:53,070
MITCH: Amazing.
Just heading to the office.

99
00:09:53,114 --> 00:09:54,898
You sound out of breath.

100
00:09:54,942 --> 00:09:56,900
Yeah.

101
00:09:56,944 --> 00:09:59,860
I almost missed Joey and Luke's
pickup this morning,
I'm running so late.

102
00:09:59,903 --> 00:10:01,644
Gotcha.

103
00:10:01,688 --> 00:10:05,387
Hey, did, uh... Did Danny call?
He didn't... He didn't show up.

104
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:07,302
Frankie, sweetheart.
It's time to go.

105
00:10:07,345 --> 00:10:08,433
Uh...

106
00:10:08,477 --> 00:10:10,784
No. No messages.
Not that I know of.

107
00:10:10,827 --> 00:10:13,482
I'm sorry.
I'm trying to get Frankie
out the door. [PANTING]

108
00:10:13,525 --> 00:10:15,092
MITCH: Okay.
Yeah, hun.
No worries, babe.

109
00:10:15,136 --> 00:10:17,834
You got a couple minutes
for one of your amazing
pep talks?

110
00:10:17,878 --> 00:10:20,184
-I need to nail this thing.
-Yes, of course.

111
00:10:20,228 --> 00:10:23,405
-Uh, what time are they due in?
-Two hours.

112
00:10:23,448 --> 00:10:26,669
We have an hour to pitch
the, uh, entire design package.

113
00:10:26,713 --> 00:10:28,410
Need ten minutes, tops, babe.

114
00:10:28,453 --> 00:10:29,846
You're my biggest fan.

115
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:32,066
Yeah, speaking of biggest fan,

116
00:10:32,109 --> 00:10:35,112
Rachel called, left a message
while we were at dinner
the other night,

117
00:10:35,156 --> 00:10:36,940
and, um, she passed
her real estate exam,

118
00:10:36,984 --> 00:10:39,551
so we are going to go out
this weekend and celebrate.

119
00:10:39,595 --> 00:10:42,685
Well, then maybe we'll all have
something to celebrate
this weekend.

120
00:10:42,729 --> 00:10:44,513
Hey, I'm just pulling up now.

121
00:10:44,556 --> 00:10:46,080
Okay, sweetheart. You got this.

122
00:10:46,123 --> 00:10:47,603
-Love you.
-I love you.

123
00:10:49,431 --> 00:10:51,694
-Okay.
-FRANKIE: I'm ready to go, Mom.

124
00:10:51,738 --> 00:10:53,696
[SIGHS] Bless your heart.

125
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:57,221
[LAUGHS] All right, stinker.
We got some work to do.

126
00:10:57,265 --> 00:10:59,049
-Come with me.
-You don't like my shirt?

127
00:11:07,144 --> 00:11:08,319
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

128
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,935
-Kate.
-Hey, Mitch. Support is ready.

129
00:11:16,197 --> 00:11:17,198
Robert.

130
00:11:19,113 --> 00:11:20,680
-Good to see you.
-Good to see you.

131
00:11:20,723 --> 00:11:22,551
-How are you?
-Great.

132
00:11:22,594 --> 00:11:24,727
MITCH: Gentlemen,
how was your flight down from...

133
00:11:27,121 --> 00:11:28,818
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

134
