presents many challenges.
Am I right, Kate?

135
00:11:38,741 --> 00:11:41,222
Tell me what you don't like
about Wholesome Grocer.

136
00:11:41,265 --> 00:11:44,051
Better yet, I'll tell you.

137
00:11:44,094 --> 00:11:49,012
Parking, pricing,
impulse stacking, clientele.

138
00:11:49,056 --> 00:11:52,973
But you're not Wholesome Grocer,
and that's exactly what we want
the consumer to know.

139
00:11:53,016 --> 00:11:56,411
The second case,
we build Green Acres.

140
00:11:58,108 --> 00:11:59,414
Not just a TV show.

141
00:11:59,457 --> 00:12:01,242
[BELLS TOLLING]

142
00:12:12,601 --> 00:12:13,602
RICHARD: Joanna.

143
00:12:14,559 --> 00:12:15,647
Does your head hurt now?

144
00:12:16,518 --> 00:12:17,606
JOANNE: Better, love.

145
00:12:18,825 --> 00:12:21,958
The morning brought
a small sense of relief.

146
00:12:25,657 --> 00:12:27,007
[WATER RUNNING]

147
00:12:30,619 --> 00:12:31,751
[SIGHS]

148
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:35,755
[SIGHS]

149
00:12:37,495 --> 00:12:38,496
Thank you.

150
00:12:43,588 --> 00:12:45,503
Perhaps you should
stay in bed today.

151
00:12:45,547 --> 00:12:48,202
Maybe today is not your day.

152
00:12:48,245 --> 00:12:51,379
[CHUCKLES] But every day
is my day, you know that.

153
00:12:59,082 --> 00:13:00,301
Just give me a minute.

154
00:13:49,698 --> 00:13:51,787
[PHONE RINGING]

155
00:13:53,789 --> 00:13:55,747
Hey, Mom, where are you?
What's going on?

156
00:13:55,791 --> 00:13:57,924
MOTHER: You need to sit down,
sweetheart.

157
00:13:57,967 --> 00:14:01,057
It's about Danny and Rachel
and the boys.

158
00:14:01,101 --> 00:14:02,319
What's going on?

159
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,626
They okay?

160
00:14:04,669 --> 00:14:07,716
Rachel's gone.
And one of the boys and...

161
00:14:08,717 --> 00:14:09,892
[SOBBING] And Danny, too.

162
00:14:09,936 --> 00:14:11,241
What do you mean, gone?

163
00:14:11,285 --> 00:14:13,330
I just...
I just heard from
Rachel last night.

164
00:14:13,374 --> 00:14:16,812
MITCH: The idea is to give
the shop an organic feeling
without the...

165
00:14:17,944 --> 00:14:20,076
crunchy granola feeling
mixing the...

166
00:14:22,992 --> 00:14:24,776
Creative with the practical.

167
00:14:24,820 --> 00:14:25,908
I'm so sorry.

168
00:14:25,952 --> 00:14:27,257
Kate, can you take over?

169
00:14:27,301 --> 00:14:29,085
[INDISTINCT WHISPERED CHATTER]

170
00:14:35,613 --> 00:14:37,398
Kate, I guess it's your floor.

171
00:14:37,441 --> 00:14:38,878
KATE: Yeah, of course.

172
00:14:38,921 --> 00:14:40,140
MOTHER: Danny killed Rachel

173
00:14:40,183 --> 00:14:42,272
and one of the boys
last night.

174
00:14:42,316 --> 00:14:45,972
