181
00:15:01,422 --> 00:15:02,423
No.

182
00:15:10,997 --> 00:15:12,346
Danny...

183
00:15:12,389 --> 00:15:15,088
Danny would never
hurt the kids, so...

184
00:15:15,131 --> 00:15:16,393
And...

185
00:15:19,744 --> 00:15:24,010
And if... And if Rachel was...

186
00:15:24,053 --> 00:15:26,708
If they were having problems,
Rachel would have told me.

187
00:15:29,537 --> 00:15:30,712
So you're wrong.

188
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:34,455
All right. We're good now.
What's up?

189
00:15:34,498 --> 00:15:35,586
TONY: Mitch.

190
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:40,591
Emily and I are on our way home
right now.

191
00:15:41,723 --> 00:15:42,767
What happened?

192
00:15:43,855 --> 00:15:44,987
It's Danny.

193
00:15:48,773 --> 00:15:50,950
[SOBBING] No.

194
00:15:50,993 --> 00:15:51,951
No!

195
00:15:56,999 --> 00:15:58,305
No...

196
00:15:58,348 --> 00:16:00,437
Oh, no, no, no!

197
00:16:03,266 --> 00:16:05,051
No!

198
00:16:05,094 --> 00:16:06,704
[MOTHER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

199
00:16:09,881 --> 00:16:10,970
No!

200
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,104
Oh, my God!

201
00:16:16,323 --> 00:16:18,542
No, no, no, no, no!

202
00:16:21,023 --> 00:16:22,068
No.

203
00:16:59,279 --> 00:17:00,280
Carolyn?

204
00:17:02,108 --> 00:17:03,152
Carolyn?

205
00:17:21,562 --> 00:17:24,260
MITCH: Listen, boys,
there's something
we got to tell you and...

206
00:17:25,783 --> 00:17:27,394
there's no easy way to say it.

207
00:17:28,308 --> 00:17:30,136
And it's gonna sound awful.

208
00:17:32,442 --> 00:17:33,617
LUKE: What happened?

209
00:17:36,142 --> 00:17:38,405
CAROLYN: I think
Danny was sick.

210
00:17:38,448 --> 00:17:40,146
You know, like...

211
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,105
sick in the head, in his mind.

212
00:17:44,889 --> 00:17:46,065
LUKE: Breakfast.

213
00:17:48,415 --> 00:17:54,290
And he... he hurt
Rachel and Evan very badly.

214
00:17:54,334 --> 00:17:55,378
He... He...

215
00:17:59,469 --> 00:18:01,254
He killed them.

216
00:18:01,297 --> 00:18:06,433
And he... he couldn't
forgive himself, he...

217
00:18:11,177 --> 00:18:12,482
He killed himself.

218
00:18:13,483 --> 00:18:15,529
[SOBS]

219
00:18:16,921 --> 00:18:18,227
Oh, I'm sorry.

220
00:18:25,756 --> 00:18:26,757
I'm sorry.

221
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:44,471
JOEY: Thank you.
MITCH: All right,
make it so, boys.

222
00:18:45,254 --> 00:18:46,255
All right, sir.

223
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:48,431
Mom?

224
00:18:50,216 --> 00:18:51,173
Be right back.

225
00:19:00,748 --> 00:19:02,053
Tuck Foxy in.

226
00:19:03,751 --> 00:19:05,492
And then have Foxy tuck you in.

227
00:19:05,535 --> 00:19:06,710
CAROLYN: I love you.

228
00:19:06,754 --> 00:19:08,364
MITCH: Yeah. Thank you.

229
00:19:12,325 --> 00:19:14,153
You, too.

230
00:19:14,196 --> 00:19:16,851
Let's get you
straightened up here.

231
00:19:17,721 --> 00:19:19,245
-Dad?
-MITCH: Yes?

232
00:19:19,288 --> 00:19:20,811
Are we all going to heaven?

233
00:19:23,553 --> 00:19:24,598
MITCH: I don't know.

234
00:19:30,821 --> 00:19:32,519
-Good night, Mom.
-Good night, my love.

235
00:19:37,437 --> 00:19:38,699
Good night. Hit the light.

236
00:19:40,962 --> 00:19:42,093
We love you, buddy.

237
00:19:56,064 --> 00:19:58,806
Oh, my God, please.

238
00:19:58,849 --> 00:20:01,243
RACHEL: Hey, sweetie,
it's Rachel.
What are you up to?

239
00:20:01,287 --> 00:20:03,158
I'm about to go take my exam.

240
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,769
And I just was calling to get
one of your famous pep talks.

241
00:20:05,813 --> 00:20:08,729
Also, it's raining here,
and I was just wondering
if it's raining there, too.

242
00:20:08,772 --> 00:20:10,078
It's really nasty here.

243
00:20:15,257 --> 00:20:16,215
Joanna?

244
00:20:17,651 --> 00:20:19,043
Where you going?

245
00:20:19,087 --> 00:20:20,741
I need to see them.

246
00:20:20,784 --> 00:20:22,221
I need to help.

247
00:20:22,264 --> 00:20:23,874
What are you
going to say to them?

248
00:20:25,006 --> 00:20:28,923
Brief is life, but love is long.

249
00:20:32,361 --> 00:20:33,754
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

250
00:20:35,843 --> 00:20:37,758
MITCH: According
to this report,

251
00:20:37,801 --> 00:20:41,240
they found Danny's car
by accident.

252
00:20:41,283 --> 00:20:44,112
A couple of hikers
came across the tracks
and followed them to....

253
00:20:44,155 --> 00:20:46,419
The edge of a ravine.

254
00:20:46,462 --> 00:20:48,072
We're lucky
