1045
01:05:55,168 --> 01:05:56,474
Hey, sweetie, it's Rachel.

1046
01:05:56,517 --> 01:05:58,215
I'm calling you
because I have an exam

1047
01:05:58,258 --> 01:06:00,652
and I just wanted to get
one of your famous pep talks.

1048
01:06:00,695 --> 01:06:03,829
Also, it's raining
really nasty right here,

1049
01:06:03,872 --> 01:06:06,527
and I wondered
if it's raining there, too...

1050
01:06:06,571 --> 01:06:07,876
Carolyn.

1051
01:06:09,791 --> 01:06:11,315
...talk to you soon.
Love you, girl.

1052
01:06:15,536 --> 01:06:17,538
Were you listening
to Rachel's message again?

1053
01:06:17,582 --> 01:06:19,888
[SIGHS]

1054
01:06:19,932 --> 01:06:23,457
Actually, you know, I don't...
I don't... [SIGHS]
I don't really listen to it.

1055
01:06:23,501 --> 01:06:24,893
Actually, that's not true.

1056
01:06:24,937 --> 01:06:26,504
-Yeah, it is.
-No.

1057
01:06:26,547 --> 01:06:28,810
It bothers me that you can't
be honest with me right now...

1058
01:06:28,854 --> 01:06:30,421
So I listen to it sometimes.

1059
01:06:30,464 --> 01:06:32,336
I don't understand
why it's a bad thing.

1060
01:06:32,379 --> 01:06:34,860
It's comforting to me
to hear Rachel's voice.

1061
01:06:34,903 --> 01:06:38,168
You don't understand
how much I need
a comforting voice right now.

1062
01:06:38,211 --> 01:06:40,909
-I don't understand, huh?
-No, you don't.

1063
01:06:40,953 --> 01:06:46,263
I've been dealing with this
right alongside you
the whole time.

1064
01:06:46,306 --> 01:06:51,659
Okay? And it... it frustrates me
that I can't figure out
how to move on.

1065
01:06:51,703 --> 01:06:53,792
-[MOANS]
-Move past it!

1066
01:06:54,358 --> 01:06:55,489
It's killing me!

1067
01:06:59,102 --> 01:07:03,497
Well, I don't listen to it
over and over again,
if that's your concern.

1068
01:07:03,541 --> 01:07:06,196
-You're lying to me.
-I'm lying?

1069
01:07:06,239 --> 01:07:09,547
You wanna talk about lying?
How about you
and your secret investigations?

1070
01:07:09,590 --> 01:07:10,939
Your late night phone calls,

1071
01:07:10,983 --> 01:07:12,985
coming home after the boys
have gone to bed,

1072
01:07:13,029 --> 01:07:14,813
sneaking in
and then checking up on me.

1073
01:07:14,856 --> 01:07:16,815
You don't understand
what I'm going through.

1074
01:07:16,858 --> 01:07:18,599
You don't care! You don't care.

1075
01:07:18,643 --> 01:07:21,776
You care only about yourself,
so leave me alone about this.

1076
01:07:24,344 --> 01:07:26,085
Why are you guys so mad?

1077
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:29,828
Oh, no... Sweetheart.

1078
01:07:29,871 --> 01:07:31,090
Honey...

1079
01:07:31,134 --> 01:07:32,657
[MITCH SIGHS]

1080
01:07:32,700 --> 01:07:34,311
We're not, baby. We're...

1081
01:07:35,964 --> 01:07:37,140
Say good night to daddy.

1082
01:07:38,271 --> 01:07:39,490
Good night, buddy.

1083
01:07:39,533 --> 01:07:41,318
-Good night.
-Come on.

1084
01:07:41,361 --> 01:07:43,494
I'm sorry we woke you up,
sweetheart.

1085
01:07:44,756 --> 01:07:46,453
We'll get you a pillow.

1086
01:07:46,497 --> 01:07:47,802
Get all cuddled in.

1087
01:07:49,195 --> 01:07:51,371
Hey, sweetie. It's Rachel.
What are you up to?

1088
01:07:51,415 --> 01:07:53,939
Uh, I am about
to go take my exam

1089
01:07:53,982 --> 01:07:57,160
and I was just calling to get
one of your famous pep talks.

1090
01:07:57,203 --> 01:08:00,598
Also, it's raining here
and I was just wondering
if it's raining there, too...

1091
01:08:00,641 --> 01:08:02,469
-[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
-[BEEPS]

1092
01:08:10,738 --> 01:08:12,088
[MITCH SIGHS]

1093
01:08:25,449 --> 01:08:27,103
Well, it's straight
from the heart.

1094
01:08:28,887 --> 01:08:31,716
I know people
will remember Rachel

1095
01:08:31,759 --> 01:08:34,632
as the generous
and honest person that she was.

1096
01:08:34,675 --> 01:08:35,763
It's...

1097
01:08:37,025 --> 01:08:38,723
It's truthful, as it should be.

1098
01:08:42,422 --> 01:08:44,511
I just don't feel like
this is real.

1099
01:08:46,861 --> 01:08:48,080
Hope I can do it.

1100
01:08:48,124 --> 01:08:49,647
Look...

1101
01:08:49,690 --> 01:08:53,390
people will understand that
this is very hard thing to do.

1102
01:08:53,433 --> 01:08:55,131
You just have
to have faith that...

1103
01:09:00,571 --> 01:09:02,747
-[ORGAN PLAYING]
-[CHURCH BELLS TOLLING]

1104
01:09:17,240 --> 01:09:19,155
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1105
01:10:22,740 --> 01:10:25,569
We're here to celebrate
the lives

1106
01:10:25,612 --> 01:10:28,746
of Rachel Turner
and her son Evan,

1107
01:10:28,789 --> 01:10:32,140
two beautiful souls
who were taken from us
far too soon,

1108
01:10:33,490 --> 01:10:35,274
but delivered into the hands
of the Lord.

1109
01:10:36,493 --> 01:10:39,800
The will of God
will never take you

1110
01:10:39,844 --> 01:10:42,281
where the grace of God
will not protect you.

1111
01:10:44,109 --> 01:10:46,677
Now I'd like to call on
Carolyn Bianci

1112
01:10:46,720 --> 01:10:50,420
if she would come
to the lectern
and share some words.

1113
01:11:12,224 --> 01:11:14,574
[SOBS] My name
is Carolyn Bianci [SNIFFLES]

1114
01:11:14,618 --> 01:11:16,837
and I am privileged to say that

1115
01:11:18,839 --> 01:11:21,929
Rachel had been my best friend
since ninth grade.

1116
01:11:23,931 --> 01:11:27,761
We formed
an immediate connection and...

1117
01:11:29,894 --> 01:11:33,332
and developed a bond that

1118
01:11:33,376 --> 01:11:36,553
continued for the past 26 years.

1119
01:11:42,385 --> 01:11:44,430
I knew that in Rachel
I had a friend for life.

1120
01:11:45,997 --> 01:11:47,825
We shared
a lot of our lives together

1121
01:11:47,868 --> 01:11:54,005
because she was so willing to...
to invest her time and her heart

1122
01:11:54,048 --> 01:11:55,528
into her friends.

1123
01:11:55,572 --> 01:11:57,487
And I love her
and I miss her dearly.

1124
01:11:58,836 --> 01:12:00,098
[SNIFFLES]

1125
01:12:00,141 --> 01:12:01,969
As you all know, Rachel...

1126
01:12:10,717 --> 01:12:13,154
Um, Rachel was never the type
to settle.

1127
01:12:13,198 --> 01:12:15,331
She always demanded
more of herself

1128
01:12:15,374 --> 01:12:19,073
and always wanted
the best for her family
and for her friends.

1129
01:12:19,117 --> 01:12:24,514
So in addition to raising
two wonderful boys,
Evan and Christopher,

1130
01:12:24,557 --> 01:12:27,168
whom she was so proud of,

1131
01:12:27,212 --> 01:12:31,738
she opened her home
with no hesitation to Mary Ann

1132
01:12:33,349 --> 01:12:35,829
because of her love of family

1133
01:12:35,873 --> 01:12:38,005
and her enormous heart
for others.

1134
01:12:42,532 --> 01:12:45,578
They say if you can find
one true friend in your life,

1135
01:12:45,622 --> 01:12:48,102
you are blessed,

1136
01:12:48,146 --> 01:12:52,585
and we are all so blessed
because, in Rachel,

1137
01:12:52,629 --> 01:12:54,674
we had that one true friend.

1138
01:13:00,463 --> 01:13:01,768
[SNIFFLES]

1139
01:13:09,341 --> 01:13:10,603
My husband Mitch...

1140
01:13:12,257 --> 01:13:15,782
is constantly reminding
our three sons that

1141
01:13:15,826 --> 01:13:19,133
our decisions shape our lives,

1142
01:13:21,788 --> 01:13:23,921
and ultimately,

1143
01:13:23,964 --> 01:13:26,140
shape the individuals
that we become.

1144
01:13:28,055 --> 01:13:30,449
We all have one

1145
01:13:30,493 --> 01:13:32,886
question before us today
and that question is

1146
01:13:32,930 --> 01:13:37,456
what meaning will we attach
to these events.

1147
01:13:37,500 --> 01:13:39,850
If we choose tragedy,
then we will all lose.

1148
01:13:44,332 --> 01:13:45,769
So the challenge

1149
01:13:47,597 --> 01:13:49,468
that I want to put there
for all of us,

1150
01:13:49,512 --> 01:13:51,165
including myself is,

1151
01:13:53,907 --> 01:13:55,953
is to take that piece of Rachel

1152
01:13:57,911 --> 01:14:01,175
that we were all so fortunate
to experience

1153
01:14:01,219 --> 01:14:05,179
and hold that
in their hearts forever...

1154
01:14:10,097 --> 01:14:12,273
by...

1155
01:14:12,317 --> 01:14:15,538
allowing it to inspire us

1156
01:14:15,581 --> 01:14:19,455
as mothers and fathers

1157
01:14:22,893 --> 01:14:24,155
and friends.

1158
01:14:34,774 --> 01:14:38,691
We will take
Rachel and Evan's light forward.

1159
01:15:04,543 --> 01:15:05,936
Thank you, Carolyn.

1160
01:15:19,036 --> 01:15:21,995
REVEREND: I would
regret this day forever

1161
01:15:22,039 --> 01:15:25,042
if I do not summon the courage
to speak of another.

1162
01:15:28,088 --> 01:15:32,484
We've spoken of Rachel and Evan.

1163
01:15:34,399 --> 01:15:40,318
But we have not made
mention of Danny Turner,
husband and father.

1164
01:15:40,361 --> 01:15:47,760
I'd be remiss if I did not
at least mention that he, too,
is a child of God.

1165
01:15:47,804 --> 01:15:51,808
And he, too, has passed
into another life, prematurely.

1166
01:15:51,851 --> 01:15:53,070
And he will be missed.

1167
01:15:53,113 --> 01:15:54,767
[ROARS] Got you.

1168
01:15:54,811 --> 01:15:57,770
MITCH: He said it was
a combination of
multiple stab wounds,

1169
01:15:57,814 --> 01:15:59,598
a severed carotid artery,

1170
01:15:59,642 --> 01:16:02,775
numerous blunt-force traumas,
and a broken jaw.

1171
01:16:05,517 --> 01:16:09,652
But the severed artery alone
probably caused her death.

1172
01:16:09,695 --> 01:16:13,090
Why did he kill Evan?
Why did he do that?

1173
01:16:13,133 --> 01:16:18,661
Well, Ben said, based on
physical evidence and
comments from Christopher...

1174
01:16:21,664 --> 01:16:28,192
it appears Evan
attempted to... to stop Danny
from attacking Rachel

1175
01:16:28,235 --> 01:16:31,456
and Danny lashed out,
possibly thinking Logan Vonda
was behind him.

1176
01:16:31,499 --> 01:16:32,805
I don't know what to think.

1177
01:16:36,853 --> 01:16:38,594
Why didn't he hurt Christopher?

1178
01:16:40,421 --> 01:16:44,034
Bill said Christopher
had blood on his back,

1179
01:16:44,077 --> 01:16:48,342
I'm guessing from Danny
pushing Christopher
into his room.

1180
01:16:49,996 --> 01:16:52,520
Well, maybe Danny
ran out of adrenaline,
came to his senses

1181
01:16:52,564 --> 01:16:54,131
and was able to stop
at that point.

1182
01:16:57,003 --> 01:16:58,526
Or someone intervened.

1183
01:17:03,967 --> 01:17:06,230
-[WAVES CRASHING]
-[BELLS CHIMING]

1184
01:17:26,424 --> 01:17:28,556
WOMAN: [SOFTLY] Joanna. Joanna.

1185
01:17:29,340 --> 01:17:30,646
Come back here.

1186
01:17:41,134 --> 01:17:44,050
You are so sweet.
You know he's going
to understand.

1187
01:17:44,094 --> 01:17:46,531
But we have to let him sleep.
It's his birthday.

1188
01:17:48,011 --> 01:17:49,577
I'm gonna surprise him anyway.

1189
01:17:50,230 --> 01:17:51,492
Okay.

1190
01:17:51,536 --> 01:17:53,320
Go on outside, okay?

1191
01:17:53,364 --> 01:17:54,539
Okay.

1192
01:17:57,760 --> 01:18:00,197
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1193
01:18:06,594 --> 01:18:09,467
[YOUNG JOANNA HUMMING]

1194
01:18:20,826 --> 01:18:22,872
[WIND BLOWING]

1195
01:18:23,873 --> 01:18:25,875
[WIND CHIMES CHIMING]

1196
01:18:25,918 --> 01:18:27,137
Ha!

1197
01:18:48,506 --> 01:18:50,029
[GASPS]

1198
01:18:59,996 --> 01:19:01,301
[ECHOING] Daddy?

1199
01:19:01,345 --> 01:19:02,650
Daddy!

1200
01:19:05,958 --> 01:19:06,959
Daddy!

1201
01:19:10,789 --> 01:19:12,095
[WATER DRIPPING]

1202
01:19:12,138 --> 01:19:14,793
Jo, shh.
What has gotten into you?

1203
01:19:14,837 --> 01:19:16,708
Mom, I know something's wrong.

1204
01:19:16,752 --> 01:19:20,059
I saw this big blue balloon
come out the window
and go into the sky.

1205
01:19:20,103 --> 01:19:23,062
JOANNA'S MOTHER: What happened?
What do you mean,
a big blue balloon?

1206
01:19:23,106 --> 01:19:26,718
I saw this big blue balloon
and it flew away
and took Daddy with it.

1207
01:19:26,762 --> 01:19:28,154
[SIGHS]

1208
01:19:28,198 --> 01:19:29,590
Daddy is okay.

1209
01:19:30,417 --> 01:19:32,158
Why don't you set the table

1210
01:19:32,202 --> 01:19:33,812
and I'll go wake him up?

1211
01:19:33,856 --> 01:19:35,727
Okay? All right.

1212
01:19:44,518 --> 01:19:47,521
Please, God. Please, God.
Please, God. Please.

1213
01:19:47,565 --> 01:19:49,567
JOANNA'S MOTHER:
[SCREAMING] Honey!

1214
01:19:50,437 --> 01:19:53,745
Oh, God, no. He's gone!

1215
01:20:29,389 --> 01:20:30,826
[PHONE RINGING]

1216
01:20:36,222 --> 01:20:38,398
This is Mitch Bianci.

1217
01:20:38,442 --> 01:20:41,184
BEN: Listen, I thought about it
after our talk and...

1218
01:20:42,185 --> 01:20:43,534
I know where Vonda is.

1219
01:20:44,665 --> 01:20:46,885
Where?

1220
01:20:46,929 --> 01:20:49,105
Well, you were right.
His actions are not of a man

1221
01:20:49,148 --> 01:20:51,803
who just happened to be
at the wrong place
at the wrong time.

1222
01:20:51,847 --> 01:20:54,850
But you need to
understand something.
He did not do this.

1223
01:20:57,635 --> 01:20:59,463
Where is he?

1224
01:20:59,506 --> 01:21:01,291
Promise me you won't
hurt him, Mitch.

1225
01:21:03,162 --> 01:21:05,208
Look, I know how important
this is to you,

1226
01:21:05,251 --> 01:21:08,211
and that's why I didn't
tell you at the diner, okay?
So just promise me.

1227
01:21:09,777 --> 01:21:11,910
I think you need
to hear it from him.

1228
01:21:11,954 --> 01:21:13,825
I think it's the only way.

1229
01:21:37,457 --> 01:21:39,546
[SOFTLY] Please, please, please.

1230
01:21:39,590 --> 01:21:41,244
Please, God, please.

1231
01:21:43,246 --> 01:21:44,900
Oh, my God, please.

1232
01:21:46,640 --> 01:21:48,729
[SOBBING]

1233
01:21:48,773 --> 01:21:52,124
I can't take this anymore,
I can't take this anymore,
I can't take this anymore.

1234
01:21:53,082 --> 01:21:54,822
I want it to stop.

1235
01:21:54,866 --> 01:21:56,476
[PRAYING INDISTINCTLY]

1236
01:21:57,869 --> 01:22:00,393
[PRAYING INDISTINCTLY]

1237
01:22:05,007 --> 01:22:07,313
I'm begging you, I beg you.

1238
01:22:07,357 --> 01:22:10,577
At least a million times a day,
I beg you, please...

1239
01:22:10,621 --> 01:22:13,319
Please just make it stop.

1240
01:22:17,933 --> 01:22:22,328
Why? Why, why? Why does
this world seem so miserable?

1241
01:22:22,372 --> 01:22:24,069
So... and...

1242
01:22:25,505 --> 01:22:31,163
and... [CRYING] fruitless,
and hopeless, and random?

1243
01:22:32,948 --> 01:22:35,211
[LOUDER] I don't understand.

1244
01:22:35,254 --> 01:22:39,476
Help me understand,
I wanna know why.

1245
01:22:41,565 --> 01:22:43,349
I wanna know why.

1246
01:22:46,439 --> 01:22:48,441
[CAROLYN CONTINUES SOBBING]

1247
01:22:54,360 --> 01:22:55,666
CAROLYN: Please.

1248
01:22:55,709 --> 01:22:58,190
Help me stop thinking
about this, please.

1249
01:23:03,717 --> 01:23:04,718
Please, God.

1250
01:23:10,159 --> 01:23:11,290
Help me.

1251
01:23:21,474 --> 01:23:23,868
[RAINDROPS PATTERING]

1252
01:23:36,837 --> 01:23:38,100
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1253
01:24:03,255 --> 01:24:04,648
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

1254
01:24:10,045 --> 01:24:12,612
MITCH: I'm looking
for Logan Vonda.
Does he live here?

1255
01:24:12,656 --> 01:24:14,179
My name is Mitch Bianci.

1256
01:24:16,573 --> 01:24:18,183
I was a friend
of Danny Turner's.

1257
01:24:22,492 --> 01:24:24,407
I know who you are.

1258
01:24:24,450 --> 01:24:25,930
How'd you find me?

1259
01:24:28,541 --> 01:24:30,021
I've got nothing to say to you.

1260
01:24:31,066 --> 01:24:32,806
All right? Leave me alone.

1261
01:24:34,156 --> 01:24:36,027
I just want to talk to you.

1262
01:24:36,071 --> 01:24:38,290
Get a better idea
of what Danny did that night.

1263
01:24:38,334 --> 01:24:39,726
I know you weren't to blame.

1264
01:24:39,770 --> 01:24:42,512
I said all I'm going to say.

1265
01:24:42,555 --> 01:24:45,254
Already said everything
to the cops.

1266
01:24:45,297 --> 01:24:47,299
MITCH: Can you just
come out for a sec?

1267
01:24:47,343 --> 01:24:48,909
I'm not looking for trouble.

1268
01:24:48,953 --> 01:24:50,868
I'll pay you for information.

1269
01:25:00,312 --> 01:25:01,444
How much?

1270
01:25:09,756 --> 01:25:11,280
LOGAN: So, what do you
want to know?

1271
01:25:15,153 --> 01:25:17,634
Why did Danny ask you
to come to the house that night?

1272
01:25:23,074 --> 01:25:25,642
I want to hear it from you
because this whole thing is...

1273
01:25:25,685 --> 01:25:27,992
[INHALES AND EXHALES DEEPLY]

1274
01:25:29,472 --> 01:25:31,691
And Danny was my friend,
and I need to know.

1275
01:25:33,911 --> 01:25:35,434
You want to know why.

1276
01:25:38,307 --> 01:25:40,787
I don't know.

1277
01:25:44,269 --> 01:25:47,272
All I know is what he told me.

1278
01:25:47,316 --> 01:25:50,623
I don't know,
it was just some...
some made-up stuff.

1279
01:25:53,235 --> 01:25:55,150
He was trying to make it
look like I did it.

1280
01:25:57,195 --> 01:25:59,241
He was going to use
that shotgun on me.

1281
01:26:01,112 --> 01:26:02,418
After he killed Rachel.

1282
01:26:04,507 --> 01:26:07,553
Make it look like self-defense.

1283
01:26:09,555 --> 01:26:12,645
And to save his wife,
he'd have to kill me.

1284
01:26:19,391 --> 01:26:20,784
Did you go into the house?

1285
01:26:22,655 --> 01:26:24,570
After Danny said
he was going to kill her,

1286
01:26:24,614 --> 01:26:26,355
why would I set foot
in that house?

1287
01:26:26,398 --> 01:26:28,270
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1288
01:26:33,144 --> 01:26:37,714
I'd just been out front,
making it look like a...
a break-in.

1289
01:26:37,757 --> 01:26:39,019
I ain't stupid.

1290
01:26:42,153 --> 01:26:44,503
How did you sleep
with all the yelling
and screaming?

1291
01:26:45,765 --> 01:26:47,637
And where did Danny
get a shotgun?

1292
01:26:48,899 --> 01:26:50,335
You wanna know the truth?

1293
01:26:51,118 --> 01:26:52,990
That's all I want.

1294
01:26:53,033 --> 01:26:56,036
I was... I was holding on
to a couple of Oxys.

1295
01:26:57,255 --> 01:26:59,214
I was saving 'em
for when I got home.

1296
01:27:02,652 --> 01:27:05,089
After he went in the house
that last time, I...

1297
01:27:05,742 --> 01:27:07,091
I popped 'em.

1298
01:27:09,441 --> 01:27:10,747
Just nodded out.

1299
01:27:11,878 --> 01:27:13,619
[EXHALES]

1300
01:27:20,147 --> 01:27:21,366
Just one last question.

1301
01:27:24,761 --> 01:27:28,286
When Danny told you
he was gonna kill Rachel,
why didn't you do anything?

1302
01:27:31,071 --> 01:27:34,336
I don't know,
go to the neighbors,
call the cops.

1303
01:27:36,120 --> 01:27:37,991
You could have
saved their lives.

1304
01:27:38,035 --> 01:27:40,342
You really think I don't wish
I did things different?

1305
01:27:45,347 --> 01:27:46,870
I live with this every day.

1306
01:27:48,480 --> 01:27:52,441
Knowin' that if...
if I'd... helped,

1307
01:27:52,484 --> 01:27:54,443
I'd done something, anything...

1308
01:27:56,836 --> 01:27:59,709
Rachel, Evan, they...
they could still be alive.

1309
01:27:59,752 --> 01:28:00,971
I know that.

1310
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:08,326
I...

1311
01:28:08,370 --> 01:28:09,893
I don't want your money.

1312
01:28:38,008 --> 01:28:39,401
Joanna Larson.

1313
01:28:45,189 --> 01:28:47,322
So happy to meet you.

1314
01:28:49,715 --> 01:28:51,369
Rachel asked that I come.

1315
01:28:53,371 --> 01:28:54,851
[CRYING] She...

1316
01:28:56,026 --> 01:28:57,201
I'm Carolyn.

1317
01:28:57,244 --> 01:28:58,855
I know.

1318
01:29:00,683 --> 01:29:02,075
I...

1319
01:29:02,119 --> 01:29:04,339
I'm sorry, do I know you?

1320
01:29:04,382 --> 01:29:06,471
We've never
personally met until now,

1321
01:29:06,515 --> 01:29:10,170
but I've been thinking about you
a great deal these few days.

1322
01:29:11,824 --> 01:29:13,739
-Why am I here?
-Yes.

1323
01:29:13,783 --> 01:29:17,134
And why have I been
thinking about you
given we don't know each other?

1324
01:29:17,177 --> 01:29:22,008
A perfectly reasonable question
to ask someone who just
showed up at your house.

1325
01:29:23,227 --> 01:29:24,489
May I come in?

1326
01:29:24,533 --> 01:29:26,056
Yes.

1327
01:29:26,099 --> 01:29:27,318
-Yeah?
-Yes.

1328
01:29:44,291 --> 01:29:45,815
Have you figured it out yet?

1329
01:29:48,992 --> 01:29:50,689
I was sent here to help you.

1330
01:29:53,562 --> 01:29:55,738
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1331
01:29:55,781 --> 01:29:59,089
I wasn't really gonna take them,
but the doctor said
they would make me feel better.

1332
01:29:59,132 --> 01:30:00,307
Uh...

1333
01:30:03,049 --> 01:30:07,314
You said Rachel
asked you to come.
What did you mean?

1334
01:30:07,358 --> 01:30:09,404
JOANNA: Life changes
in an instant,

1335
01:30:10,361 --> 01:30:12,276
the ordinary instant.

1336
01:30:12,972 --> 01:30:14,496
Joan Didion.

1337
01:30:14,539 --> 01:30:15,758
Yes, exactly.

1338
01:30:16,933 --> 01:30:18,630
"To choose between
darkness and light."

1339
01:30:18,674 --> 01:30:20,415
"And that
we always have free will."

1340
01:30:20,458 --> 01:30:25,028
JOANNA: And when
a tiny nub of truth

1341
01:30:25,071 --> 01:30:27,552
makes a lie seem real,

1342
01:30:27,596 --> 01:30:31,556
it blurs our choices
like there are two voices
inside your head.

1343
01:30:32,601 --> 01:30:33,602
Tell me something.

1344
01:30:34,820 --> 01:30:36,692
When you're upstairs,

1345
01:30:36,735 --> 01:30:42,306
in that sacred spot,
praying on your knees,

1346
01:30:42,349 --> 01:30:45,570
you believe that
God hears you, don't you?

1347
01:30:46,876 --> 01:30:48,007
I want to.

1348
01:30:49,182 --> 01:30:51,271
I want to so badly.

1349
01:30:54,710 --> 01:30:58,061
But every day, I wake up...

1350
01:30:59,758 --> 01:31:05,416
and I just feel the same
pain and grief and hurt, and...

1351
01:31:07,374 --> 01:31:10,116
and, you know, I just...
I have these horrible...

1352
01:31:11,248 --> 01:31:12,641
thoughts.

1353
01:31:14,120 --> 01:31:16,122
Who... How'd you...

1354
01:31:17,428 --> 01:31:19,604
How do you know where I...

1355
01:31:19,648 --> 01:31:22,868
Because it was shown to me.

1356
01:31:22,912 --> 01:31:24,827
That morning, Carolyn,

1357
01:31:24,870 --> 01:31:28,961
I awoke with the natural
to a particularly angry dawn.

1358
01:31:30,180 --> 01:31:31,834
CAROLYN: The natural?

1359
01:31:31,877 --> 01:31:35,751
Are... are you saying
you see things
when they happen?

1360
01:31:35,794 --> 01:31:39,145
You saw these murders happen?

1361
01:31:39,189 --> 01:31:40,886
Not so like I'm seeing you.

1362
01:31:42,105 --> 01:31:44,542
This is something different.

1363
01:31:44,586 --> 01:31:49,852
More like how Mitch saw Rachel
a few days before the funeral.

1364
01:31:54,030 --> 01:31:56,162
How could you
possibly know that?

1365
01:31:56,206 --> 01:32:01,603
Oh, it all started the day I saw
my father pass away.

1366
01:32:01,646 --> 01:32:03,474
[WIND CHIME CHIMING]

1367
01:32:03,518 --> 01:32:05,694
[JOANNA CHUCKLES]

1368
01:32:05,737 --> 01:32:12,352
Since that morning, I found
that I could look at someone

1369
01:32:12,396 --> 01:32:18,271
and know if he's at risk,
because darkness
had him in its grip.

1370
01:32:29,674 --> 01:32:33,722
[CAR HORN BLARING]

1371
01:32:33,765 --> 01:32:34,984
[TIRES SQUEAL]

1372
01:32:36,333 --> 01:32:39,510
JOANNA: Sometimes,
I was able to help.

1373
01:32:40,380 --> 01:32:42,208
Other times...[CHUCKLES]

1374
01:32:43,383 --> 01:32:46,082
free will takes over,

1375
01:32:46,125 --> 01:32:51,870
and then a person may make
the very worst decision.

1376
01:33:02,011 --> 01:33:03,055
As did Danny.

1377
01:33:04,883 --> 01:33:10,062
Ironically enough,
I had two occasions
to help Danny.

1378
01:33:12,587 --> 01:33:15,764
It only takes one bad decision.

1379
01:33:17,592 --> 01:33:21,117
CAROLYN: Does the darkness
ever let go?

1380
01:33:22,118 --> 01:33:23,380
JOANNA: Maybe, Carolyn.

1381
01:33:24,990 --> 01:33:27,776
But Danny is in heaven.

1382
01:33:31,475 --> 01:33:34,696
Oh, gosh.
Things have a way of...

1383
01:33:34,739 --> 01:33:37,916
well, changing
as the universe directs.

1384
01:33:39,265 --> 01:33:41,485
It's a spiritual contract.

1385
01:33:43,618 --> 01:33:45,358
And it's out of our control.

1386
01:33:46,795 --> 01:33:49,493
Sometimes, I think of it...

1387
01:33:49,536 --> 01:33:51,713
more as a responsibility
that I've been given.

1388
01:33:53,628 --> 01:33:55,760
But I believe... No.

1389
01:33:55,804 --> 01:34:00,112
I know that
I have been selected
to help where I can.

1390
01:34:01,723 --> 01:34:06,336
Oh, oh, oh,
I have so much to tell you.

1391
01:34:06,379 --> 01:34:09,513
But it's important
that your husband
be a part of the conversation.

1392
01:34:34,799 --> 01:34:36,235
JOANNA: Oh...

1393
01:34:36,279 --> 01:34:39,586
He's been suffering so much,
I'm worried about him.

1394
01:34:39,630 --> 01:34:42,024
CAROLYN: I don't know
where he is.
We've been fighting.

1395
01:34:42,067 --> 01:34:43,678
I woke up this morning
and he was gone.

1396
01:34:43,721 --> 01:34:46,593
-I would call the office...
-He's on his way home to you...

1397
01:34:47,377 --> 01:34:48,465
right now.

1398
01:34:50,380 --> 01:34:51,642
Time for me to go.

1399
01:34:55,864 --> 01:34:57,735
This is my address.

1400
01:34:57,779 --> 01:35:00,738
Visit me tomorrow
with your husband

1401
01:35:00,782 --> 01:35:01,957
and feel better.

1402
01:35:03,567 --> 01:35:04,786
Help is on the way.

1403
01:35:07,092 --> 01:35:08,441
[DOOR OPENING]

1404
01:35:09,573 --> 01:35:10,748
[DOOR CLOSING]

1405
01:35:12,663 --> 01:35:14,796
-[CAR DOOR CLOSING]
-[ENGINE STARTING]

1406
01:35:17,407 --> 01:35:18,800
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

1407
01:35:24,544 --> 01:35:26,721
-CAROLYN: Mitch?
-Hey, listen. I found...

1408
01:35:26,764 --> 01:35:29,462
I just met
the most amazing woman. She...

1409
01:35:31,464 --> 01:35:35,033
She said that Rachel
sent her here to help us.

1410
01:35:36,165 --> 01:35:37,732
MITCH: I found Logan Vonda.

1411
01:35:40,299 --> 01:35:41,692
You what?

1412
01:35:41,736 --> 01:35:47,089
Before you say anything, I...
I... I'm glad I did.

1413
01:35:47,132 --> 01:35:52,224
Because now I... I...
I understand why Danny
did what he did, but... but...

1414
01:35:53,922 --> 01:35:56,446
Not why he did what he did,
but how it happened.

1415
01:36:02,191 --> 01:36:04,149
She said Danny is in heaven.

1416
01:36:04,193 --> 01:36:05,585
MITCH: No, no, no.

1417
01:36:06,630 --> 01:36:09,154
Uh... Danny made his choice.

1418
01:36:11,896 --> 01:36:13,768
She said that
you would say that. She...

1419
01:36:15,770 --> 01:36:17,380
She told me to tell you...

1420
01:36:19,861 --> 01:36:22,254
the butterfly thinks
you have beautiful eyes.

1421
01:36:37,487 --> 01:36:40,620
MITCH: There's something
I'd like to do
before we go visit Joanna.

1422
01:36:43,232 --> 01:36:45,234
I'd like to
stop by Nicholson Quarry.

1423
01:36:46,888 --> 01:36:48,367
Why would you wanna do that?

1424
01:36:50,239 --> 01:36:51,806
it seems appropriate.

1425
01:37:21,357 --> 01:37:23,620
BEN: I was chatting with
the owners of the quarry.

1426
01:37:23,663 --> 01:37:26,797
I think we ought to put
a metal fence between
those two trees back there.

1427
01:37:26,841 --> 01:37:30,148
They're afraid it might become
one of those places
where people come and...

1428
01:37:30,192 --> 01:37:32,237
-You know?
-Golden Gate Bridge.

1429
01:37:32,281 --> 01:37:33,369
Yeah.

1430
01:37:37,112 --> 01:37:38,591
I didn't expect
to find you here.

1431
01:37:39,505 --> 01:37:41,333
I come here whatever I can...

1432
01:37:41,377 --> 01:37:43,509
looking for something.

1433
01:37:43,553 --> 01:37:45,163
Maybe the same reason
you're here now.

1434
01:37:48,514 --> 01:37:50,473
Listen, what if I told you

1435
01:37:50,516 --> 01:37:54,477
that we uncovered evidence
of financial trouble
in the Turner household?

1436
01:37:54,520 --> 01:37:57,697
Maybe even some
marital problems.

1437
01:37:59,438 --> 01:38:00,875
Would that make a difference?

1438
01:38:02,964 --> 01:38:04,139
No.

1439
01:38:05,749 --> 01:38:06,924
Not anymore.

1440
01:38:11,189 --> 01:38:12,321
Okay.

1441
01:38:13,800 --> 01:38:15,150
I'm gonna go now.

1442
01:38:16,629 --> 01:38:18,936
Let me know if you find
what you're looking for.

1443
01:38:32,471 --> 01:38:34,343
[ENGINE STARTS]

1444
01:38:36,432 --> 01:38:38,086
[ENGINE STARTS]

1445
01:39:13,251 --> 01:39:20,258
I have felt Rachel's presence
so many times since she died.

1446
01:39:20,302 --> 01:39:24,828
But I... I just...
I convinced myself
that I was imagining things.

1447
01:39:28,179 --> 01:39:32,618
And then yesterday
when I met Joanna,
she told me that... that...

1448
01:39:32,662 --> 01:39:36,579
That Rachel's soul lives on,
and sometimes our souls,
they... they intersect.

1449
01:39:38,929 --> 01:39:40,452
Joanna was in the church.

1450
01:39:42,280 --> 01:39:43,978
She sat in the very last pew.

1451
01:39:50,114 --> 01:39:53,726
She told me Rachel
was proud of me
for speaking on her behalf.

1452
01:39:56,773 --> 01:39:58,993
She was standing next to me
at the altar

1453
01:39:59,036 --> 01:40:01,256
and I felt it. I felt it. I...

1454
01:40:04,085 --> 01:40:05,129
I felt it.

1455
01:40:08,002 --> 01:40:09,307
MITCH: Yeah, I felt it, too.

1456
01:40:12,876 --> 01:40:14,965
Hi, I'm Richard.

1457
01:40:15,009 --> 01:40:16,662
You must be Carolyn and Mitch.

1458
01:40:17,402 --> 01:40:19,535
I've been expecting you.

1459
01:40:19,578 --> 01:40:22,059
MITCH: Like when Rachel was
standing in the doorway
laughing and smiling.

1460
01:40:22,103 --> 01:40:24,322
CAROLYN: Yeah, she was there.
She was there.

1461
01:40:24,366 --> 01:40:27,717
When Joanna and I were talking,
she was there.

1462
01:40:27,760 --> 01:40:29,023
Sanctuary night.

1463
01:40:30,981 --> 01:40:32,156
Beautiful, isn't it?

1464
01:40:38,119 --> 01:40:39,120
RICHARD: Hmm.

1465
01:40:52,611 --> 01:40:55,658
If God cares about the grieving,
why wouldn't he prevent it?

1466
01:40:59,705 --> 01:41:02,143
RICHARD: I don't know
how she does it,

1467
01:41:02,186 --> 01:41:06,886
but anything she touches
just seems to grow and grow.
[CHUCKLES]

1468
01:41:06,930 --> 01:41:09,280
Joanna says it's because
of all the conversations

1469
01:41:09,324 --> 01:41:12,022
she's had with the trees
over the years.

1470
01:41:12,936 --> 01:41:14,372
Ah. There she is.

1471
01:41:14,416 --> 01:41:16,200
-I'll see you later.
-CAROLYN: Thank you.

1472
01:41:20,335 --> 01:41:21,988
-JOANNA: Mm.
-[CAROLYN CHUCKLES]

1473
01:41:36,177 --> 01:41:38,788
Is that why we're here, Mitch?

1474
01:41:38,831 --> 01:41:41,269
Why you refuse to believe
that he's in a better place?

1475
01:41:41,312 --> 01:41:43,140
I don't know
if I can ever forgive him.

1476
01:41:46,100 --> 01:41:49,233
I don't know,
but I have to believe
that he's in heaven. I...

1477
01:41:50,234 --> 01:41:51,627
I have to believe that.

1478
01:41:51,670 --> 01:41:52,845
No.

1479
01:41:54,325 --> 01:41:55,848
Mitch...

1480
01:41:55,892 --> 01:41:58,460
Why would a murderer like Danny
be allowed into heaven?

1481
01:42:00,723 --> 01:42:02,464
[INHALES DEEPLY]

1482
01:42:02,507 --> 01:42:03,639
[SIGHS]

1483
01:42:06,685 --> 01:42:11,299
You know, I never once saw
Danny in a bad mood.

1484
01:42:11,342 --> 01:42:15,303
Always had a smile on his face,
and I've known him a long time.

1485
01:42:15,346 --> 01:42:16,826
Heck, he introduced us.

1486
01:42:19,481 --> 01:42:22,614
I've never even seen him
lose his temper, not once.

1487
01:42:24,964 --> 01:42:26,966
You know, I mean, he didn't...

1488
01:42:27,010 --> 01:42:30,144
He didn't do everything right.
He... didn't work very hard,

1489
01:42:31,623 --> 01:42:33,582
didn't manage
his finances very well,

1490
01:42:33,625 --> 01:42:36,237
but if you knew him like I did,

1491
01:42:36,280 --> 01:42:40,110
you would say that he led
a happy and productive life.

1492
01:42:42,678 --> 01:42:46,986
And then to murder
your wife and your kid...

1493
01:42:48,858 --> 01:42:50,338
and then to kill yourself...

1494
01:42:55,865 --> 01:42:57,475
it makes no sense.

1495
01:43:36,297 --> 01:43:39,256
So I just... I...
I need to understand.

1496
01:43:39,300 --> 01:43:43,347
You understand
more than you realize, Mitch.

1497
01:43:43,391 --> 01:43:46,785
Danny's easygoing nature
was a mask

1498
01:43:46,829 --> 01:43:49,266
and was the result of his fears.

1499
01:43:49,310 --> 01:43:51,921
A fear of not being good enough.

1500
01:43:51,964 --> 01:43:53,618
A fear of failure.

1501
01:43:54,793 --> 01:43:57,274
A fear of not being loved.

1502
01:44:13,856 --> 01:44:17,425
[MITCH INHALES DEEPLY AND SIGHS]

1503
01:44:20,471 --> 01:44:23,474
JOANNA: That's what drove him
to always be nice,

1504
01:44:23,518 --> 01:44:26,390
so that he would
always be liked.

1505
01:44:26,434 --> 01:44:29,437
But Danny had anger in him,

1506
01:44:31,047 --> 01:44:32,222
a darkness.

1507
01:44:32,266 --> 01:44:34,659
Ah.

1508
01:44:34,703 --> 01:44:37,401
JOANNA: The fact that he wore
a mask to disguise it
didn't make it any less real.

1509
01:44:37,445 --> 01:44:42,058
In fact, it made it
all the more explosive
when it finally came out.

1510
01:44:42,101 --> 01:44:43,668
You love them too much.

1511
01:44:43,712 --> 01:44:45,540
Yeah, sure.

1512
01:44:45,583 --> 01:44:48,325
That don't mean that
sometimes I don't feel
like pointing it all west

1513
01:44:48,369 --> 01:44:51,763
and just driving to some town
where no one can find me.

1514
01:44:53,199 --> 01:44:55,724
JOANNA: Because he thought
of himself as unworthy.

1515
01:44:55,767 --> 01:44:58,248
So he tried
to compensate by lying,

1516
01:44:58,292 --> 01:45:01,556
and cheating, pretending
he was something he wasn't.

1517
01:45:02,905 --> 01:45:05,168
He fought with the darkness,

1518
01:45:05,211 --> 01:45:07,997
and lost again and again

1519
01:45:08,040 --> 01:45:10,739
because he stopped
trusting in God.

1520
01:45:12,044 --> 01:45:13,394
Without trust...

1521
01:45:14,743 --> 01:45:16,222
there is no faith.

1522
01:45:18,399 --> 01:45:21,053
Yes, we do have free will.

1523
01:45:21,837 --> 01:45:24,883
Yes, we do make mistakes.

1524
01:45:25,797 --> 01:45:29,975
Yes, we all experience darkness.

1525
01:45:31,237 --> 01:45:35,024
Two angels appeared
at Danny's bedside

1526
01:45:35,067 --> 01:45:38,244
the night before and said,

1527
01:45:38,288 --> 01:45:41,465
"Do not do
what you are about to do."

1528
01:45:47,732 --> 01:45:51,649
Those angels attempted
to convert Danny's thinking,

1529
01:45:51,693 --> 01:45:53,869
to show him
there was another way.

1530
01:46:07,709 --> 01:46:13,671
But the lure of darkness
was impossible
for Danny to resist.

1531
01:46:13,715 --> 01:46:18,937
He was given the opportunity
to choose darkness and light.

1532
01:46:20,939 --> 01:46:22,419
In his confusion,

1533
01:46:22,463 --> 01:46:26,075
it was the darkness
that appeared to be the truth.

1534
01:46:26,118 --> 01:46:29,208
I said, "We always have
free will, Danny."

1535
01:46:30,558 --> 01:46:32,603
That's what
I tried to remind him of.

1536
01:46:33,865 --> 01:46:35,824
But I knew he wouldn't listen.

1537
01:46:39,784 --> 01:46:41,177
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1538
01:46:46,922 --> 01:46:49,272
[DANNY WHIMPERING]

1539
01:46:53,755 --> 01:46:55,844
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1540
01:47:03,242 --> 01:47:05,723
[DANNY SCREAMING]

1541
01:47:06,898 --> 01:47:08,552
[GRUNTING]

1542
01:47:08,596 --> 01:47:10,162
JOANNA: I seized
the opportunity

1543
01:47:10,206 --> 01:47:11,860
to push him towards the light.

1544
01:47:11,903 --> 01:47:13,427
[STRAINING]

1545
01:47:15,820 --> 01:47:17,431
VOICE: [WHISPERING]
Cut the cord.

1546
01:47:19,084 --> 01:47:20,477
Cut the cord.

1547
01:47:20,521 --> 01:47:23,567
JOANNA: For a moment
I thought we had won.

1548
01:47:31,357 --> 01:47:33,447
Then the darkness overtook him.

1549
01:47:35,579 --> 01:47:38,582
It pushed him towards
the lamp and shouted...

1550
01:47:38,626 --> 01:47:40,236
VOICE: It's too late
to turn back.

1551
01:47:40,279 --> 01:47:43,805
Don't you stop now.
Don't you stop, Danny.

1552
01:47:45,067 --> 01:47:46,460
Don't stop.

1553
01:47:46,503 --> 01:47:48,462
JOANNA: The instant
he sliced that cord,

1554
01:47:49,506 --> 01:47:50,681
and picked up the lamp,

1555
01:47:54,729 --> 01:47:57,079
he was prodded up the stairs.

1556
01:47:57,122 --> 01:47:58,776
VOICE: It's too late
to turn back.

1557
01:48:01,518 --> 01:48:03,259
It's too late to turn back.

1558
01:48:13,965 --> 01:48:15,445
[THUNDERCLAP]

1559
01:48:18,709 --> 01:48:22,104
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1560
01:48:28,937 --> 01:48:32,723
God, don't let this happen!

1561
01:48:35,378 --> 01:48:38,294
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1562
01:48:49,131 --> 01:48:53,831
God, don't let this happen!

1563
01:48:53,875 --> 01:48:57,095
Now the darkness gave him
one last nudge.

1564
01:49:01,143 --> 01:49:04,625
It works a million times a day
all over the world.

1565
01:49:04,668 --> 01:49:09,194
A tiny nub of truth that...
that makes a lie seem real.

1566
01:49:15,505 --> 01:49:17,594
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1567
01:49:48,059 --> 01:49:50,148
[JINGLING]

1568
01:49:53,369 --> 01:49:55,676
[STIRRING]

1569
01:50:01,943 --> 01:50:04,032
[RACHEL STIRRING]

1570
01:50:07,122 --> 01:50:08,123
RACHEL: Danny?

1571
01:50:12,736 --> 01:50:15,478
What? [GROANS IN PAIN]

1572
01:50:16,697 --> 01:50:20,396
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

1573
01:50:22,528 --> 01:50:24,530
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

1574
01:50:37,761 --> 01:50:40,590
[SCREAMING]

1575
01:50:40,634 --> 01:50:41,809
EVAN: What are you doing?

1576
01:50:45,247 --> 01:50:48,903
JOANNA: After Rachel,
he lashed out at Evan.

1577
01:50:48,946 --> 01:50:52,602
He was told he was doing
the best thing for his son,
so he believed it.

1578
01:50:53,298 --> 01:50:55,170
[EVAN SCREAMING]

1579
01:50:55,213 --> 01:50:57,607
I begged God to stop him.

1580
01:50:57,651 --> 01:50:59,914
Stop it now!

1581
01:51:00,697 --> 01:51:02,394
And fell to my knees.

1582
01:51:03,918 --> 01:51:05,310
And perhaps I was heard.

1583
01:51:06,529 --> 01:51:07,922
[DANNY WHIMPERING]

1584
01:51:09,619 --> 01:51:10,881
I will never know.

1585
01:51:14,755 --> 01:51:20,804
[CRYING] Hey... Hey...
put some shoes on, buddy.

1586
01:51:20,848 --> 01:51:24,678
Can't run around the house
with no shoes on, come on.
Put some shoes on.

1587
01:51:31,772 --> 01:51:34,383
Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

1588
01:51:34,426 --> 01:51:38,866
Shh. It's okay. It's okay.
Go back to bed.

1589
01:51:41,869 --> 01:51:44,741
JOANNA: He was on his way
to kill Christopher,

1590
01:51:47,135 --> 01:51:50,355
when finally an angel blocked
Christopher's doorway

1591
01:51:50,399 --> 01:51:52,706
and told Danny, "Stop.

1592
01:51:52,749 --> 01:51:55,230
"You are not taking this one."

1593
01:51:57,667 --> 01:52:00,626
Those words
brought Danny to his senses,

1594
01:52:01,758 --> 01:52:03,804
and saved Christopher.

1595
01:52:06,197 --> 01:52:08,460
I want you
to consider something.

1596
01:52:14,292 --> 01:52:18,993
Perhaps it will
help you to understand
the power of forgiveness.

1597
01:52:22,953 --> 01:52:24,825
[CRYING]

1598
01:52:24,868 --> 01:52:26,391
Please forgive me.

1599
01:52:30,178 --> 01:52:32,702
JOANNA: You can
remain angry at Danny.

1600
01:52:33,921 --> 01:52:35,749
You can hate him.

1601
01:52:35,792 --> 01:52:38,926
You can hope
that he rots in hell,

1602
01:52:40,101 --> 01:52:42,059
punished
for the rest of eternity.

1603
01:52:42,103 --> 01:52:43,626
That's your choice.

1604
01:52:43,669 --> 01:52:49,632
But then you stay trapped
in your anger,

1605
01:52:49,675 --> 01:52:52,983
and in prison
in your own emotions,

1606
01:52:53,027 --> 01:52:56,639
because of a desire
to see another suffer.

1607
01:52:58,684 --> 01:53:00,164
Ask yourself something.

1608
01:53:02,166 --> 01:53:04,778
Do you want
to be guided by hate...

1609
01:53:06,867 --> 01:53:07,998
or by love?

1610
01:53:14,352 --> 01:53:16,311
Danny, like all of us,

1611
01:53:16,354 --> 01:53:17,965
he was a sinner as we are,

1612
01:53:18,008 --> 01:53:21,011
but his father
loved him nonetheless

1613
01:53:21,055 --> 01:53:22,796
and brought him back home.

1614
01:53:25,973 --> 01:53:28,453
God does not view sin
in different levels.

1615
01:53:28,497 --> 01:53:30,629
That was the creation of man.

1616
01:53:37,941 --> 01:53:41,205
Rachel and Evan
have forgiven him.

1617
01:53:43,904 --> 01:53:46,820
I think... you should, too.

1618
01:55:22,698 --> 01:55:25,092
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]



